Comparison of Absorption Costing and Variable Costing
Under absorption costing, all of the fixed overhead costs are matched with the revenues.
Under variable costing, only the fixed overhead that is traced to the units actually sold in a period is matched with the revenue from those units.
Under absorption, all units produced are considered to be part of the inventory and inventory costs are accumulated regardless of whether the units have been sold or not.
Under the variable method, only the units sold are considered in inventory and inventory is valued only at the variable costs.
